Today i was exploring the routing constraint. i found that when there multiple constraint in the route declaration routing fails. suppose below if is my route template
```html
/{value:double:int}/
```
and send the parameter as 15.0
Expected: Route should pass 
Actual:- it is giving error "Rout not found".

**Below is my analysis:-** 
The issue is here in the [TemplateSegment.cs](https://github.com/aspnet/Blazor/blob/e31bf2979627e91f2fe96e3bb0946293edd11568/src/Microsoft.AspNetCore.Blazor/Routing/TemplateSegment.cs#L49). Basically here when the first constraint does match but the second constraint does not match, still it say the route does not match. even though the first constraint match
If you want to find this then run the test [CanMatchSegmentWithMultipleConstraints](https://github.com/aspnet/Blazor/blob/e31bf2979627e91f2fe96e3bb0946293edd11568/test/Microsoft.AspNetCore.Blazor.Test/Routing/RouteTableTests.cs#L197)  with
```html 
var context = new RouteContext("/15.0"); 
```

It is going to fail.
the logic might be something below
```csharp
 if (IsParameter)
            {
                matchedParameterValue = pathSegment;
                if (Constraints.Count() > 0)
                {
                    foreach (var constraint in Constraints)
                    {
                        if (constraint.Match(pathSegment, out matchedParameterValue))
                        {
                            return true;
                        }
                    }
                    return false;
                }

                return true;
            }
            else
            {
                matchedParameterValue = null;
                return string.Equals(Value, pathSegment, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase);
            }
        }
```

